e based on; including the perspectives of service users in its analyses; offering recommendations for the future design of activating policies. The book will be invaluable for students, lecturers and researchers of social and labour market policies and policy makers. It is essential reading for those interested in issues of inclusion, activation and the role of types of work in promoting inclusion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aFull employment policieszEuropean Union countries. 0aMarginality, SocialzEuropean Union countries. 0aSocial integrationzEuropean Union countries. 7aEDUCATION / Educational Policy & Reform / School Safety.2bisacsh1 aBerkel, Rik van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Marisol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGonzález, Aitor Gómez, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen, Henning, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHespanha, Pedro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHornemann Møller, Iver, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLind, Jens, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMachado, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMøller, Iver Hornemann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoche, Maurice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aValkenburg, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilliams, Colin C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 ade Schampheleire, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 avan Berkel, Rik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/